  "prompt": "Has Jay-Z ever performed together live with Panjabi MC and/or Labh Janjua?",
  "response": "Yes, Jay-Z has indeed performed live with Panjabi MC. The most notable collaboration between Jay-Z and Panjabi MC is the remix of Panjabi MC's hit track \"Mundian To Bach Ke,\" which features Jay-Z's vocals. This remix, titled \"Beware of the Boys (Mundian To Bach Ke),\" gained significant popularity in the early 2000s.\n\nThere are documented instances of Jay-Z performing this track live with Panjabi MC. One of the most famous performances was at the 2003 MTV Europe Music Awards in Edinburgh, Scotland, where they performed the song together on stage. This performance helped cement the track's success globally.\n\nAs for Labh Janjua, he was the original vocalist on Panjabi MC's \"Mundian To Bach Ke,\" providing the Punjabi lyrics that are central to the song's identity. However, there is no widely known instance of Jay-Z performing live with Labh Janjua specifically. The collaboration primarily involved Jay-Z and Panjabi MC, with Labh Janjua's vocals being a key component of the original track.\n\nIn summary, Jay-Z performed live with Panjabi MC, but there is no record of a live performance with Labh Janjua.",
